CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1956, pg. A2, reads: "Change - Over - Irene Kaufmann Settlement was changed to a new, independent agency - The Anna B. Heldman Community Center - Julian Ruslander (left), IKS president, has announced. Dr. Ralph Scott (right), local educator, will head the new agency's board.  Judge Homer S. Brown and Oliver M. Kaufmann, one of the benefactors and descendent of IKS's original donors, were among the incorporators of the community center. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Julian Ruslander, Homer S. Brown, Oliver M. Kaufmann, and Ralph Scott holding sign inscribed "Anna B. Heldman Community Center"
